/imantics/blob/master/imantics/dataset.py#L161\r\n\r\nThe method `def index(self, dataset)` of image looks ok and makes call to \r\n`annotation.index(dataset)` for each annotation in the image to index itself into the dataset. \r\n\r\n**However**, the `index` method of annotation [here](https://github.com/jsbroks/imantics/blob/88a3095e52a9246d94875bb7459990e28277c314/imantics/annotation.py#L181) is\r\n\r\n`def index(self, image)`\r\n\r\nIs that correct, shouldnt it be `def index(self, dataset)`?\r\n\r\nEdit - Just noticed, When adding an annotation to an image, annotation gets indexed to the image as well, so `def index(self, image)` is called [here](https://github.com/jsbroks/imantics/blob/88a3095e52a9246d94875bb7459990e28277c314/imantics/image.py#L146) too with image as argument.","closed_by":{"login":"jsbroks","id":24920936,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0OTIwOTM2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/24920936?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks","html_url":"https://github.com/jsbroks","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jsbroks/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jsbroks/imantics/issues/33/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jsbroks/imantics/issues/33/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"s